Two reviews taken by Australia and neither lost although one resulted in the dismissal of Bancroft. However, this time Wade survives and Australia breathe a sigh of relief.
A length ball outside off, Smith gets across and tucks it towards square leg.
A bouncer down the leg side, Steve ducks awkwardly.
FOUR! A bit too straight from Broad, the length being a bit too full as well, Smith gets across and tickles it to the fine leg fence. The deficit is now 178.
Outside off, another exaggerated leave from SS.
Outside off, left alone again.
A hat-trick of leaves to end the over.
Good delivery! Good length on off, goes a bit away from the batsman. Wade knows his off pole and leaves it alone. Also, drizzle getting heavier.

Length ball above the hips, Wade looks to flick and the ball hits Wade's gloves. The ball rolls towards square leg and the batters cross for a single. Wade is off the mark after 23 balls. Wade wrings his hand in pain.
Good bounce on this ball. It pitches on a length outside off, Smith awkwardly defends it out. It hits the handle of Smith's bat.
This time on middle, Smith flicks it towards fine leg and rotates the strike.
Good length ball on off, Wade defends it out.
Again on middle and off, Wade blocks it out towards off. 2 runs off the over.
Good length ball outside off, Smith looked to play at it but kept the bat just away. Good delivery from Broad.
Another one on the same line, Smith walks across and blocks it off his back foot.
This is on a shortish length on off, Smith blocks again.
WIDE! Goes for the bouncer but not the right line, too wide down the leg side, Smith ducks under it.
Fifth stump line on a good length, Smith leaves this alone.
FOUR! Top shot! Shortish length outside off, Smith punches this off his back foot through covers to hit the first boundary of the day.
This one is closer to off pole on a good length, Smith blocks it well and does his antics.
Outside off on a good length. Wade leaves it alone.
Fuller this time just outside off, Archer makes a good stop at mid off.
Again full outside off, this time Wade lets it be.
Good length ball just outside off, Matthew shoulders arms to this one.
Full on middle and leg, Wade flicks it towards fine leg and takes a single.

Fractionally short on middle and leg, Smith gets on one foot and pulls it towards deep square leg. He runs quickly for the first and thinks about going for the second, but decides against it. Tidy over from Stokes, just 2 off it. Australia are 89/4.
FOUR! Superb timing from Smith. Good length ball outside off, Smith punches this through point to get another boundary. No chance for the fielder there.
Slightly short this time outside off, Smith blocks this towards leg side off his back foot.
Beaten! Superb comeback! This is again on a shortish length, shapes away from the batter, Smith fends to get beaten.
Good length ball outside off, Smith pushes it towards mid-wicket to change ends.
FOUR! Fuller one outside off to the left-hander, Wade punches it through mid off superbly. Archer dives to his left to stop but fails to do so. Wade reaches 1000-run landmark with that boundary.
Fullish on off, Wade flicks it towards short mid-wicket. End of a good over for Australia. 9 off it.
Good length ball on off, Smith shuffles across and tucks it towards fine leg. Crosses ends.
Bouncer! Well directed by Archer, on off pole line. Wade ducks under it.
Good length and on off, pushed towards mid off.
On middle and leg, Wade this time shuffles across and plays it towards square leg.
This time just outside off, blocks it out.

Ouch! This bounces rapidly towards Wade, he is hit on the gloves. The ball rolls towards the leg side. It seems that the ball hit Wade on the fingers, he takes off his gloves and stretches them, he seems alright as he puts his gloves back on quickly.
Good length outside off, Smith has no business with it. After pitching shaped further away.
This one is again on a good length, closer to Smith who tucks this towards square leg to take a single. 100 up fur Australia with that run.
Full ball on middle to Wade, he flicks it straight to mid-wicket.
Good length ball, on the fourth stump, came slightly in to the batsman who blocked it well of his back foot.
Good ball! Fullish one on middle, Wade lunges to block it.
Good length ball outside off, Wade is aware of his stumps as he lets this pass to the keeper. Another one shaped into the left-hander. Tight over from Broad.
Archer steams in, bowls this one just outside off on a good length. Smith lets it be.
Good bumper. Hits the deck hard on the middle pole line, Smith ducks under it as the ball is collected by Bairstow.
Fuller on off, pushed towards cover. The fielder there stops it.
Just outside off, Smith shoulders arms to it.
Full on middle and off, Steve flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Good bouncer by Archer, Wade tries to evade it but fails to get out off the way and the ball hits his right bicep. The ball rolls towards fine leg and the batters cross for a leg bye.
Good length ball outside off, Wade is not fending at that.

OUT! Caught! Very good low catch at gully from Rory Burns. Broad goes slightly fuller outside off, the length is perfect for the drive and Wade goes for that. The shot produces an outside edge and Burns grabs that inches above the turf. One hand came off the bat when Wade went for the drive. Wade's struggle is over.
Shortish one to the skipper to start with. Rises a bit after coming into the batsman, Paine blocks it well.
Looked for another good length ball outside off, dishes a full toss, Paine mistimes it towards mid on.
Fourth stump line on a good length, Paine lets it be.
Shortish one outside off, Paine shoulders arms again. Superb over from Broad. Can be the opening England were after.
Good length ball just outside off, Smith looks to defend but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
Beaten! Nerves finally getting to Smith maybe. Archer bowls this one wide and short outside off and Smith lashes at it. However, the ball swung away a lot and just beats the blade of Smith.
Outside off, Steve shoulders arms to let that one through.
Back of a length this time, Smith defends it towards the point region.
That one was awkward. Short of a length on off, Smith lines up for the pull but backs out at the last moment to defend it. The ball kept a bit low and Smith did well to defend it out.
Outside off, Smith lets it be. Wicket maiden followed up by a maiden. England piling up the pressure here.
Full and outside off, Paine pushes this towards cover.
Outside off, the skipper taps it towards cover, looks for a single, then looks at his ex-skipper and is sent back.
On a length outside off, some extra bounce, Tim blocks it out watchfully.
Fuller in length, well blocked out.
Outside off, Tim looks to drive but the ball swings back in and goes off the inner half towards Jofra Archer at mid on.
Full and around off, this is driven compactly towards mid on. Third maiden on the trot.
Good length ball on off, Smith tucks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single. First run after 18 balls for the Aussies.
Length ball just outside off, Paine guides this one to the point fielder.
Fuller this time on off, Paine plays this back to Archer.

Oohh! Edged but falls safely. Short of a length on middle, Paine looks to pull this one but gets an inside edge onto it. The ball then hits the pads and bounces but falls safely. Close call with short leg in place.

FOUR! Educated edge this one by the skipper. Good length ball outside off, Paine looks to guide it towards third man but gets a bit of an outside edge. The ball races to the third man fence. The skipper is off the mark but with a bit of luck.
Tim shows the full face of the bat and defends this ball off the back foot.
Good length outside off, on fifth stump line, Smith leaves this one.
Good delivery but equally well played. That came in from a good length ball. Smith lunged to push it towards fine leg to change ends.
Shortish ball outside off, closer to Paine who blocks it off his back foot.
Fuller one this time, closer to the batsman, Paine leaned forward to drive past the covers, got the gap but no timing there, gets a couple.
Fifth stumper from Broad, Paine lets it go to the keeper.
Another one outside off on a good length, Paine lets it be.
Starts off with a length ball just outside off, Smith flicks it towards mid-wicket.
This time on middle, Smith pushes it back to Woakes off the back foot.
Length ball on off, Smith shuffles across and again plays it towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Gets on the back foot and flicks this towards fine leg to take a single.
Again similar line, on middle and leg, Paine flicks it to the leg side and crosses ends.
Fullish outside off. A rare edge by Smith but safe as it goes between gully and slip towards the third man region. Denly runs for it from the slip cordon and collects as the batters take two.

Ha ha ha! This is comical. How good and honest is this debutant bloke? Good length ball on off and middle, comes in to the batsman. The push towards the leg side was missed and Paine was hit high on the pads. There's an appeal from the slip cordon but Archer is not even interested! Eventually, he appeals, on seeing his mates. Root is serious though and wants to review but is informed that it is too high.
FOUR BYES! Another good length ball on leg stump, shapes away further on the leg side to go to the fence by evading the doing keeper. Paine tried his best to flick but missed.
Good length ball this time, Paine blocks it.
Shortish length to Paine, who looks to pull and does it awkwardly to get a run.
Bumper from Archer but too high, Smith not attempting anything on that one.
Another good length ball outside off, Smith pushes it to mid-wicket to take a run.
Short of a length ball outside off, Smith plays it back to Woakes.
Beaten! Good ball by Woakes here, pitches it on the fourth stump line and gets it to nip away from Smith. He goes for the block but misses. The ball keeps low and goes to JB on two bounces.
On middle and leg, Smith flicks it towards fine leg and takes a single.
Outside off, Paine chooses to leave this one.

Loud appeal by the the English for an LBW but denied by the umpire. They decide not to take the review. Looks to be going above the stumps. Good length ball just outside off, the ball nips back in after pitching. It hits Tim near the knee-roll on the middle pole line. The England players appeal loudly but nothing from the umpire. Replays later roll in and the Hawk Eye confirms that the ball was going over the middle pole. Good decision here.
Again gets beaten as Paine goes for the push outside off. End of a good over.
Good length ball outside off, Smith looks to drive but gets an outside edge. This was a slower one and hence didn't carry to the second slip fielder. That was a knuckle ball from Archer.
Shortish one to follow the good length ball, Smith blocks it well.
Looking for the yorker, Archer dishes a full toss going down leg side, Smith misses his flick on that one.
Good length ball outside off, Smith lets it be.
This time he attempts a bumper but it is too high. Smith ducks it easily.
Beaten! This doesn't happen often but Smith has been troubled twice in this over. Good length ball outside off, Smith plays at a wrong line to get beaten.
Length ball on middle and off, Paine pulls it towards leg for a single.
On the hips of Smith, he pushes it towards square leg with soft hands and takes a single.
Fuller outside off, Paine blocks it out towards covers.
This time full on the off pole, Paine does well to block this towards the off side.

Ohh! Close one this. Woakes bowls this one on a length on middle. Paine looks to push it towards covers but gets an inside edge on it as the ball rolls towards fine leg. Leach slides in near the fence and keeps the ball in play as the batters take two.

Similar to the last ball, again Tim looks to push this off the back foot towards the off side. He again gets an inside edge but this time it results in just a single. Luck is favoring Australia here in every way possible.
Full and outside off, left alone.
A short ball outside off, the skipper looks to pull but misses. Was there a noise? Naah...

EDGED, SHORT! On a length outside off, Tim looks to defend but the ball moves away and takes the outside edge. However, because he played that with soft hands, it does not carry to Jason Roy at second slip.
Outside off, quietly left alone this time.
Hit this one! What a riposte from Archer. A sharp bouncer outside off, TP sways away from the line.

Another snorter from Archer, banging it on a length outside off and then generating steep bounce. Paine looks to push at that, almost fending it away, with one hand off the bat but the ball flies off the outside edge. However, because the bottom hand came off the bat, the ball dies down even before it goes to gully. It is in the gap and the batsmen take a single.
Good length outside off from Woakes, leaves it silently.
Fuller ball this time, Paine blocks it by staying inside the crease.
FOUR! SMASHED! Wide ball outside off and a shortish one to add. Paine opens his arms and pummels it through point and cover. Superb shot.

Excellent, simply excellent from Buttler! Wow. What a piece of fielding. Total commitment. Full ball outside off, Paine pushes it towards the off side and looks for a quick single. Ben Stokes comes in from cover and has a shy at the non striker's end, but misses. Paine was in though. No one to backup as Jofra Archer is a bit wide at mid on. The ball races towards the mid-wicket fence but hello! Jos Buttler gives it a chase from deep mid-wicket, dives full length to his left and stops the ball! Three runs taken.
Good length on middle and off, Smith pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Wide outside off to finish the over. Smith leaves it alone.
Length ball on off pole, Paine plays it back to the bowler.
This one is again on middle pole, the ball pitches and nips back in as Smith gets hit on the thigh pad.

What happened there! What a ball by Archer! A seam-up delivery on a length outside off, the ball pitches and nips back in a bit, but just as it crosses Smith, the ball wildly moves to the left of Bairstow. He dives and gets a hand to it as the ball rolls towards fine leg and the batters take a bye off it. The ball doing crazy things here.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Outside off again, Smith lets it go again.
Length ball again by the bowler. Smith defends it off the back foot.
Good length ball on off and middle from Leach, Paine blocks it by lunging.
Similar line from Leach, Smith pushes this towards point.
Another good length ball but on middle and leg, Paine blocks it again.
Slightly fuller this time on off, Paine comes forward and blocks well.
Another fullish one outside off, Paine pushes it straight to the fielder at point.
Slightly short one from Leach, Paine looks to slash this but this goes straight to the fielder at point, who fumbles but no run taken.
Length outside off, Smith leaves it alone.
Again length but this time straighter, Smith tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Similar line and length, Smith shuffles and tucks it towards square leg for a couple. Making good use of the crease here.
Bouncer! Good one and on middle, Smith does well to duck under it.

Ouch! That must have hurt Smith! Stokes has a stare at him. Some fire on the pitch here. Stokes bowls this on a length and just outside off, the ball rises off the deck. It hits Smith between his thumb and forefinger, on his right hand. He has a look at the pitch and then at Stokes, who gives a stare back to him too. Fiery!
This time flicks this one towards fine leg and takes a single. 138/5 Australia with Smith and Paine hanging in.
Full on off, Smith comes forward to push it back to the bowler.
Slightly fuller on middle and leg, Smith works it towards the leg side.
Another fullish ball outside off, Smith looks to drive this through point, but straight to Broad who is lazy to get down. The ball rolls towards third man and they take three.
Oohhh... that was gone. But for the inside edge. Full and outside off, Paine looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. Leach puts in an appeal but no one does. The umpire shakes his head.
Fuller one again, Paine blocks this off the inside half of the bat.
Fuller one outside off again, Paine pushes it straight to cover.
Good length on middle and leg, Smith tucks it towards mid-wicket with soft hands. Runs the first one quickly and completes the second easily. Smith moves to 43 with this.
FOUR! Beautiful cover drive by Smith! Full and outside off, perfect for the cover drive and Smith doesn't miss out. Leans into it and smashes it to the fence.
Smith chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
On middle and leg, Smith flicks this one towards the leg side and takes one. Inching closer to his half ton.

Length ball on the off pole, it nips back in and hits Paine on the thigh pad. The English players appeal for an LBW but the umpire denies it. They surprisingly mull over taking a review as the ball seems to be going well over the wickets. In the end, they decide against taking it.
The skipper shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Fuller one outside off, Smith comes forward to push towards the off side.

FOUR! HEAVED! 25th half-century and 7th in the Ashes for Smith. Good length ball on middle and off, Smith charges down the track to go for the biggie. Doesn't time it too well but good enough for a boundary. Races to the mid-wicket fence. 150 comes up as well for Australia. Smith is in the mood again. He continues to be the thorn for England. First player to score 7 successive 50-plus scores in the Ashes. The 50-run stand comes up too!
Full and around off, driven back to the bowler.
Outside off, pushed towards Leach again.
Full and just outside off, blocked towards Leach.
Landed outside off, spinning away, Steve gets a big stride forward and watches it go past.

Down the leg side, Paine goes for the pull but doesn't time it well. It hits the top half of his bat and uppishly goes towards fine leg. Bairstow gives it a chase, collects it and the batters exchange ends. Leg bye signalled.
Length ball on leg again, Smith pulls this well towards backward square leg and gives the strike to his skipper.
Paine shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

Beaten! Now, where did this hit Paine, thigh pad, bat or glove? We think it's thigh pad. The ball pitches on a good length, just outside off pole and moves away after pitching. The ball kisses the thigh pad and goes on the bounce to first slip. Oohhs and Aahs by the crowd as well as the players. Paine was looking to defend but got squared up.
Paine has played it to the point region.
Beautifully driven to the cover fielder off this full ball outside off by Paine.
Full on middle, Smith flicks it straight to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on off, Smith blocks it well.
Fuller one this time, Smith is right in the line to block.
Fullish one this time, Smith is in total control as he blocks it well again.
Shortish one this time, outside off, Smith blocks it off his back foot.
Good length ball outside off, Smith defends the over out.
Bouncer but too high for Paine. He tries to hook but misses and the ball carries to JB. First warning for the bouncer given to Stokes.
Short of a length on the body, Paine awkwardly pulls this one towards square leg for a single.
Fuller this time, Smith flicks it towards the leg side.
Again on the body, Smith works it towards square leg.
Bouncer! Smith ducks this time as he doesn't want to take any risks just before Lunch. 2nd one for the over called by the umpire.
Outside edge off the last ball but doesn't carry to the fielder at gully. Smith survives and so do Australia. LUNCH!
First ball, full toss outside off, Paine fails to make full use of it and pushes it straight to Stokes at cover.
Beaten! Good length ball on the fourth stump line, Broad moves his fingers on this one. It pitches and moves away as it beats the outside edge of Paine's bat.
Fuller this time, Paine pushes to mid-wicket and gives Smith the strike.
Outside off, Smith leaves it alone.
FOUR! Shot of the day! Beautiful straight drive by Smith to this full pitched ball just outside off. It goes rapidly through mid off and to the fence. The deficit is below 100 now for the Aussies.
Pushed to mid-wicket by Smith. Australia start the session well, 5 off the first over after Lunch.
Good length ball on off, coming into Paine, blocks it towards mid on. Not those convincing blocks though.
Shortish one on middle, Paine pushes it towards deep square leg to take a run.
Full ball outside off, Smith pushes it towards point and says a loud no.
Shortish one outside off, Smith comes across to work it towards mid-wicket to take a single.
Bumper this time, a bit too high as Paine ducks under it easily.

OUT! Caught! Good captaincy from Root as he persisted with that short leg fielder ever after the 50-run stand. This came in from a slightly shortish length on off, Paine looked to work it towards mid-wicket but gets an inside edge, the ball goes to hit his thigh pad and lob in the air to Buttler who pouches that comfortably at short leg. Early strike for England after Lunch. Archer has his second.
Good length just outside off, Smith blocks it towards point.
Broad bowls this one full and on off, it pitches and stays a bit low. Smith does well to block it towards the off side.
Full again outside off, Smith plays this towards covers with just a hint of the outside half of his bat. The ball goes to deep cover where the fielders gobble it up and the batters take two.

FOUR! Beautiful flick off the pads! One moment we think he's gonna get out plumb in front of the wickets but he just flicks it gracefully for a boundary. Full and on middle, Smith shuffles across and nonchalantly plays it towards the mid-wicket fence.
Smith has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Outside off, Smith leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Cummins looked to push it towards point with a dab. Pushed it nicely towards third man. Takes three to get off the mark on first ball.

Good idea from Archer but the line was wrong. Looked for a slower yorker to pin Smith in front of the stumps, misses the line on that one. Remember how Bumrah had got the wicket of Shaun Marsh during Border-Gavaskar Trophy during India's last tour to Australia.
Slightly fuller outside off, Smith pushes it towards cover to take a run.
FOUR! That was intentional but risky. Fourth stump line outside off, Cummins goes with the shot and manages to thread the slip and gully cordon to get a boundary.
Bumper from Archer but too high for Cummisn to do anything there.

FOUR! What was that? Sharp incoming delivery from outside off, Cummins looks to block it off his back foot but the ball shoots up off the surface to get past the bat. Bairstow fails to collect that even with a leap and it races to the fine leg fence.

Full and around middle, Smith looks to flick but the ball goes off the inside edge, onto the pads and lobs towards short leg. But where is short leg? Has Root missed a trick here? Cummins wnts a single but Steve sends him back.
Comes forward again and whips it towards short mid-wicket.
Tossed up on middle, Smith pushes it to mid on and takes a single.

Ohh! The English team appeal for an LBW but denied by the umpire. Tossed up on middle, the ball goes down with the angle. Cummins looks to flick but misses to get hit on the front pad. The England team appeals in unison but the umpire denies it. The replays roll in and it seems the ball is going down the leg side. Good that the hosts didn't take the review.
Full on off, pushed back to Leach.
This time tossed up outside off, pushed to covers.
Shortish length outside off, Smith walks across and blunts this on the off side.
FOUR! Thumped through the covers. Fuller on but wide outside off. Smith has a chance to open the arms. He slams that one through covers and no one moves. Races to the fence.
WIDE! Bumper this time, called wide as Smith ducks.
Slightly shortish but coming into the batsman, Smith blocks it bit awkwardly.
Outside off on fifth stump, Smith lets it alone.
Another bumper but again too high. Bairstow leaps to take it into the gloves.

OUCH! On the elbow. Wow. Archer has hit Smith on the body and gets the crowd going. Finally gets the line right for the bumper. This doesn't rise much as Smith looks to duck, gets hit on the elbow. Looks in a lot of pain there.
Floated on middle and off, Cummins plays it back to Leach.
This time flatter, Cummins takes a foot forward but gets an outside edge on it. The ball goes off the leading edge towards covers. Falls way short of the fielder.
The batsman has played it to the point region.
Full and floated just outside off, it goes uppishly towards point off the leading edge of Cummins' bat.
Full on the pads, Cummins pushes it towards mid on.
Cummins flicks this one towards the leg side.

FOUR! Goes for the bouncer. Archer is not going to stop doing that seeing Smith's pain. Good ball, on the body as Smith looks to pull this, gets a top edge and the ball flies over the keeper for a four. Smith not looking to hang back either.

Another bouncer! Superb bowling from Archer. This is heading towards the head of Smith, he moves across and looks to hammer over the square leg fielder. Didn't time it well, in the air but lands safe, short of deep backward square leg. They take one.
Fullish ball on off, Cummins blocks it well but Jofra has overstepped.

Barrage of bouncer continues from Archer, this time to Cummins. The ball flies off the surface as Cummins gets beaten. Bairstow leaps to pouch that one goes for an appeal. Root goes for the review at the very last moment, that looked close. However, replays shows that it was very far from the willow or gloves of Cummins. Review gone for England.
Good length on off, Cummins pats it towards point.
Outside edge now! Outside off on a good length from Archer as Cummins looks to push it towards the off side. Gets an edge and lands between slip and gully. They take a run.

Beautiful bowling by Archer! Truly rock and roll! Making life as hard as he can for Smith. Length ball and it rockets off the pitch. It rises on Smith and hits him on the glove.The ball lobs towards Jos Buttler at short leg but just too far from him. He dives but doesn't get to it. Looks like the wicket of Smith is coming soon following the injury on his elbow, however he is toughing it out right now.
Full and outside off, pushed towards cover.
Around middle and off, pushed back to the bowler.
Full on middle, pushed towards the bowler again, this time towards mid on.
Full and around middle, this time Cummins nudges it wide of Buttler at short leg for a quick single.
Around middle, solidly defended.
Tossed up around middle, Steve drives it straight back. Leach collects and mimes a throw but does not release it.
Archer bowling short ball after short ball. This time Cummins ducks and it gets through to Bairstow.
FOUR! Beautiful drive by Cummins. This time he bowls it full but outside off. Cummins leans into the drive and the ball races to the cover boundary.
Mixing it up well here Archer. This time Archer bowls it on a length, the ball pitches just outside off and nips away. Cummins tries to defend but misses as he gets squared up.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Again beaten, the wicket doesn't seem to be far away from Archer here. Length ball outside off, Cummins tries to put bat on ball but misses again.
The batsman fails to put bat on ball.
Fuller ball on off, Smith drives it firmly towards mid off and takes for a quick single. There is a direct hit but he is home comfortably.
Good length ball on off and middle, Cummins blunts it comfortably.
This is slightly shorter on off, Cummins blocks it again.
Same line and length, Cummins is behind the ball to block again.
Another shortish length on off, blocked by Cummins on the off side.
Fuller this time, Cummins dabs this off his front foot.

FOUR! Short again by Archer but pulled well by Smith, just wide of the fielder at backward square leg where Stokes was positioned. The ball was going uppishly and the England players were excited for a moment but the ball races to the fence. 200 up with that boundary.

Nasty! Very Nasty this one by Archer! And Smith is down on the floor this time as the ball has hit him flush on the NECK! Archer bowls this short and just outside off, it shoots off the pitch. Smith looks to duck under it but the ball didn't bounce as much as he expected. He bends down awkwardly in an attempt to leave it but fails to do so. The ball hits him on the side of his neck. He's lying on the ground shaking his head.
Fuller one to the new man, this one is just outside off, Siddle pushes it towards mid off to take a run. Off the mark on ball one.
Shortish ball on middle to Cummins, Looks to guide towards the leg side but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Another shortish one on the body to Cummins, he stands tall to this one and blocks.
Beaten! Good ball! Shortish length on off, shapes back into the batter who plays down the wrong line to get beaten.
Flat on middle, Siddle blocks it out towards the off side.
Flat on middle, pushed back to Leach.
Again flat on middle, pushed to covers.
Floated this time, pushed back to the bowler.
Quick single taken by the batters. Siddle pushes it towards covers and doesn't react quickly to the call of his partner, however he does make it to the other end in time. Single taken.
Blocked towards the point region off the front foot by Cummins.
Another bumper! 95 mph this time but too short as Siddle ducks under it.
Beaten again! Good length ball on off, comes in with the angle. Siddle looks to have a push at it but gets beaten.
Another short ball. Again very high as Bairstow jumps to collect it over his head.
Now slower yorker from Archer. Siddle read it early to block it well.
Mixing it up here is Archer, slower bouncer outside off. Siddle evades it.
Fullish outside off, Siddle pushes it back to the bowler by presenting full face of the bat.
Pitched outside leg, blocked by Cummins.

Some turn off the pitch for Leach, the ball pitches outside leg and goes over the off pole as Cummins misses his defensive block. Bairstow isn't able to grab it on the first time but it doesn't result in any damage.
On the legs of Cummins, he flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
Siddle defends it by getting on the front foot towards the leg side.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

FOUR! Much-needed boundary after a long time for Australia. The ball is on the leg side, Siddle nudges it towards fine leg and the ball slowly trudges to the fine leg fence. Burns gives it a chase from square leg but fails to keep the ball in play.
Full and down the leg side, left alone.
Another one down the leg side, Pat looks to tuck but misses. Archer appeals for a caught behind but nothing from Bairstow.
Around off, solidly defended.
A length ball down the leg side, Patrick misses his flick and is hit on the pads.
A bouncer, on middle, PC ducks.

FOUR BYES! Not anyone's mistake, to be honest. Yes, Archer slides this down the leg side but the ball pitches and scoots further away from Jonny Bairstow who cannot get to it with a dive. All the way to the fine leg fence. This stand is worth 11 now.

LBW appeal! Woakes starts with a good length ball on middle, this comes in from the off stump and hit Siddle on the pads. An appeal from English players but that looked to be missing leg. Hawk Eye confirms the same.
Fifth stump line outside off, Siddle leaves it alone.
Shortish length on middle, Siddle pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Beaten! Outside off on a good length, Siddle looks to push but is beaten. Good delivery.
Shortish ball on middle, goes further down the leg side as Siddle misses his flick.
Wide outside off, left alone. Woakes starts with a maiden.
Outside off, left alone by Cummins.
On the legs of Cummins, he tries to flick but misses to get hit on the thigh pad. They take a leg bye off this as the ball rolls towards backward square leg.
Swing and a miss! Full outside off, Siddle looks to drive it through the covers but misses as the ball whizzes past the outside edge. Good bowling by Broad.
Full outside off, Siddle drives at this one too. The ball skews off the outside edge and goes between gully and the slip cordon. Denly mops it up from the deep as the batters take three.
Beauty! Length ball, fourth stump line, nipping away. A fast bowler's dream! The only thing missing was the outside edge as Cummins looked to defend but did so inside the line. He survives this one.
Defended off the back foot by the Cummins.
Good length outside off, Siddle has no business with that one.
Shortish ball on off, came into the right-hander quickly as his flick is missed, gets hit on the back leg.
Another shortish one, looked a slower one. Siddle tucked it towards the leg side bit awkwardly.
Goes for a fuller on this, Siddle leans forward to block it back.
Another fuller one from Woakes, Siddle bends down a bit to block it again.

Huge appeal! Fuller again from Woakes, Siddle looks to flick this with his wrists but is very slow at it. The ball thuds into the pads and England fans make a loud appeal but that looked to be missing leg. No reviews taken. Might have been an edge as well.
Length ball on leg pole, Cummins tries to block this one out but he gets an inside edge on it and the ball goes towards square leg.
Outside off, on a length, Cummins looks to play at that but misses.
Wide outside off stump, the batsman leaves it alone.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Bouncer! The batsman ducks under the bouncer at the last moment.
On a length outside off, Cummins looks to defend but the ball stays low and goes off the outside edge towards cover.
Slightly shorter one on middle, Siddle looks to block towards the leg side but gets a small leading edge that falls close to him.

OUT! Caught! Beauty from Woakes to get rid of Siddle. Shortish length on off from Woakes, Siddle looks to fend at the ball which shapes a tad bit away from him, gets an edge which is pouched by Bairstow comfortably. A dodgy knock comes to an end from Siddle. Australia still trail by 40.
Good length ball on off, Smith has his normal walk across to tuck it towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! WOW! Who said Smith was retired hurt just a while ago! Length ball on off, Smith clears his front leg and slams this towards mid-wicket. What a shot from Smith that.

FOUR! Wow, what a return to the crease for this man here! This is just pure class from Steve. Length ball just outside off, goes on the back foot and just creams this towards the cover fence. Consecutive boundaries by Smith.
Short ball just outside off, Smith lets this one go. The man is back to the crease and he is looking for the ton here.
Good length outside off, Cummins lets this one go to the keeper.
Shortish one from Woakes which came in, Cummins was right behind the line of the ball to block.
Wide one outside off, Cummins is not bothered, lets it go to the keeper.
Beaten! Fuller on off, asking Cummins to go for the drive. Cummins obliges to the bowler as he looked to drive but gets beaten on the inside edge.
Slightly short one outside off, Pat taps it towadrs point.

Good length ball but goes down the leg, Cummins looks to flick but misses. There was a noise but it was probably off the ball kissing the pad. A mild appeal from a few English players but nothing from the umpire.

FOUR LEG BYES! Woof! Bairstow will be relieved here as the ball has hit the thigh pad and not on the bat! Down the leg side, Smith looks to flick but misses. The ball hits the thigh pad and trudges towards the fine leg fence.
Smith gets an inside edge and the ball hits him on the pads.

FOUR! Full this time outside off, Smith goes for the drive but gets an outside edge on it. The ball goes between gully and the slip cordon towards the third man fence. Looking shaky a bit here Steve Smith.

A loud appeal for LBW but denied by the umpire. Full outside off, Smith shuffles across, looks for the block but misses. He  gets hit low on the back pad but the impact seems outside off. Replays roll in, and Hawk Eye comes that it was missing the off pole as well. Smith living dangerously here.

OUT! LBW! Woakes gets rid of Smith for 92! Wow. That is something unimaginable, isn't it? Steve not getting an Ashes ton. Would have been his third successive ton this series and also the fourth in the Ashes. Would have been the first player ever to do so. Woakes has done the trick. A length ball, outside off, the former skipper gets across but then shoulders arms. Big, big mistake. A rare moment of indecision from Smudge. He is hit on the pads and immediately starts to walks off even before umpire Gaffaney raises his finger. However, Cummins calls him back and asks him to go for the review. Smith's reaction is like, 'Oh, come on, mate! But fine.' Signals the 'T'. Hawk Eye comes in and shows it to be hitting the stumps. End of another knock which has probably saved the day and match for the Aussies. A magnificent 92. Steve Smith departs but only after a standing ovation from the home of cricket. He came out after getting injured and played bravely. Australia now trail by 24. A one-inning shootout awaits us.
The batsman has attempted to put bat on ball but fails.
Good length outside off, Cummins blocks coming forward. Wanted a single but decided against it.
Shortish one from Broad, that shaped down the leg side, Cummins looks to tuck it around but missed. No edge there.

Dropped! That was half a chance for sure. Shortish one outside off, Cummins looks to slam this over point but gets an outside edge which flies towards second slip. The ball was slightly higher but Roy couldn't get his jump to perfection and the ball didn't stick in his hands. The batters meanwhile take a single.
Fullish one outside off, Lyon blocks it well.
Going down the leg side this time, misses his flick.
Going down again, Lyon goes for a flick but misses again.
Fullish ball on off, Cummins blocks it coming forward.
Slightly fuller on fourth stump, Cummins lunges to block it back to the bowler.
Fullish outside off again, Cummins drives it straight to the cover fielder. Came off from the toe end of the bat.
Good length on off, Cummins taps it towards point.
Goes fuller on middle this time, Cummins pushes it straight to the fielder at mid-wicket.
Fullish one again outside off, Cummins pushes it towards mid off, again came off from the toe end of the willow.
Beaten! That kept low. Fullish length around off stump, Lyon looks to push towards mid on, gets beaten. The ball dies down as it goes to Bairstow.
That sounded good off the bat but straight to the fielder. Fuller outside off, Lyon punches it straight to covers.
Now a shortish length, on a good height to be pulled but Lyon misses as he gets an inside edge into his body.
Gets his pull right this time as Broad dishes out another short one, gets off the mark with a single through mid-wicket.
Fullish on the leg pole, Cummins works it towards fine leg to change ends.
Bumper again but Lyon is up for the battle. Pulls this towards deep square leg to get a run. Good timing on that one from Lyon.

Great catch by Jonny Bairstow! No? My ears are ringing then. A length ball down the leg side, Lyon looked to tuck but missed. Jonny dived to his left and took it with one glove. Went up in an appeal but Woakes says he did not hear anything. Good that Root does not review. Replays show that it went off the shirt.
A length ball around off, solidly defended.
Full and outside off, pushed straight to cover.
Lovely shot but for nothing. Full and outside off, Garry drives this straight back but Woakes bends and stops it with his left hand.
A length ball, down the leg side, helped through mid-wicket for a run.

EDGED, FOUR! Did that carry? Not sure. A length ball outside off, Cummins pushes at it but the ball flies off the outside edge. The ball goes low to Ben Stokes at third slip who gets down to his left but cannot stop it, or catch it. Third man records another boundary. Cummins moves to 20 now.
Bouncer outside off from Broad, Lyon goes for a pull but misses. Played on a wrong line there.
That was in the air! Fuller ball on off, Lyon lofted it towards mid off uppishly but no fielder there. Leach runs from short extra cover to stop the ball. They take three.
Shortish around off, Cummins blocks it off his back foot.
Another shortish length to which Cummins lunges to block.
Fuller ball outside off, Cummins looked to drive this through the off side but it came off the inner half of the bat to roll towards Broad. On good days, this disturbs the timber.
Outside edge now but doesn't carry. Good length outside off, Cummins fends at this but gets an outside edge. Root is in perfect position to gobble that but it just falls short of England skipper.

OUT! LBW! The decision stays as it is. Leach gets a wicket as well. Full and around leg, Lyon looked to defend but missed and got hit on the pads. leach appealed as soon the ball missed the bat, umpire Gaffaney thought long and hard and then raised his finger. Lyon looked at Cummins and then signalled the 'T'. Hawk Eye comes in and initially we are unable to understand whether the ball has clipped or hit the stumps. Lyon is asked to go and after some time, we come to know that the ball has hit the stumps. No reviews left for Australia now.
Full and outside off, pushed towards cover.
Spinning in from outside off, worked through square leg for a single.
Down the leg side, Pat looks to flick but misses. The ball goes through the vacant fine leg region and the batsmen take a leg bye.
Outside off, solidly defended.
Full and outside off, Hazlewood drives this through the covers and gets a couple. 250 up for Australia! The deficit is now 8.
Shortish ball on off, coming in to the right-hander who blocks it off his back foot.
Good length ball on off, Cummins blocks it off his back foot again.

OUT! Caught! Goes for a bumper but this is going down the leg side, Cummins goes for a massive pull to heave this over the mid-wicket fence. He is late into the shot and as the ball passes his attempt, it kisses the gloves. Bairstow goes to his left to grab that easily. Broad has his fourth. England manage to stay 8 runs ahead.
Right on target immediately. A length ball, around off, left alone.
Off the mark. A length ball, tucked past short leg for a single.
A length ball, around off, Roy gets squared up a touch and pushed it towards short mid-wicket.
A length ball around off, Jason taps this awkwardly to the off side.
A length ball outside off, JR pushes this watchfully towards the slip cordon.
Length ball outside off, stays a touch low, Roy looks to defend but the ball stays low and goes off the bottom edge towards mid off.
FOUR! Length ball just outside off, Burns stands tall and punches this off the back foot towards the cover fence. Lyon gives it a chase but sloppily lets it go through for a boundary.
Good defense off the back foot on this length ball outside off.
Length ball outside off, Burns lets it go.
Bouncer this time, Rory does well to evade it.
Fuller this time but on middle and leg, Rory flicks it in the gap between mid on and mid-wicket and takes a couple.
Down the leg side again, Burns looks to flick but misses.
Cummins pitches this on middle and off and the ball goes further away as Roy misses his flick.
Shortish around the fourth stump line, Roy blunts it close to the body off his back foot.
Fuller ball around off, Roy blocks it solidly.
Shortish one, rising a bit but Roy works it nicely through deep backward square leg for one. Roy off the mark with that single.
Bumper this time to the left-hander but the line is down the leg side and it is too high, Rory ducks under it.
Beaten! Good delivery in the channel outside off. Burns looks to push and is beaten all ends up. Good end to the over from Cummins.
Shortish length on middle and off, comes in with the angle to hit on the stomach as Roy misses his flick.
Shortish but wide outside off, Roy is not lured at that one.
Edged but didn't carry! This again is in the channel outside off. Roy has a poke at this without any feet movement. Gets an outside edge but the ball doesn't carry to the second slip fielder.
Shortish ball on middle and leg, Roy works it towards fine leg to get off strike.
Too high! Pitched short on middle and off but this goes high again.
This time in the channel of uncertainty to the left-hander. Rory knows his off stump and leaves it alone.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Cummins takes the first wicket of this English innings and Roy is dismissed for a paltry score of 2 runs. Cummins bowls this one short and on the body of Roy, he looks to flick it towards fine leg but gets a top edge on it. The ball loops behind Cummins and he runs back and catches it. Jubilation for Australia as Roy is out of here and England are 1 down for just 9 runs.

OUT! Caught! Massive blow for England. What a delivery first up to the England captain. Cummins is again in the channel for the right-hander. Root is new to the crease and wants to feel the first ball as he pokes at it and gets a thick edge to skipper Paine who is not going to miss out on that. Body blow this one. Australians smelling blood now.
No hat-trick for Cummins. A length ball outside off, coming in a long way, Denly misses his tuck and is hit on the pads.
Outside off, in the avenue of apprehension, left alone.
Another leave outside off.
Outside off, on a length, JD looks to defend but the ball comes in a long way and beats the inside edge! Top over from Cummins. A DOUBLE WICKET MAIDEN!
Good length on off, Rory taps it on the off side.
Short ball on middle this time, Burns ducks under it nicely.
Good length outside off, came in after passing the batsman. A good leave from Burns though.

IN THE AIR... SAFE! Shortish ball on the body, Burns looks to defend but the ball lobs towards Usman Khawaja at gully who is late to react as the ball drops very close to him. He got out similarly in the 2nd innings of last Test.
Another short ball, Burns evades this nicely.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Burns works it towards mid-wicket. They take a couple.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Denly.
Good length ball on off again, Denly gets the inner half of his bat on it and the ball rolls towards mid on.
FOUR! Short ball down the leg side this time by Cummins, Denly trying to keep it down gets a glove on this one and the ball races towards the fine leg fence.

On the hips of Denly, he looks to flick but misses his shot. It hits the thigh pad and the ball rolls towards backward square leg as Hazlewood there collects it. While collecting the ball, Hazlewood fell down almost doing a split. He quickly gets up and the batters take two in the meantime.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Fuller on the legs, Denly pushes this towards mid-wicket.
Bouncer on the hips down the leg side, Burns looked to work it around but is hit on body. No run taken there.
Shortish one outside off, taps it off the back foot towards the off side.
Bouncer again but outside off, Burns converge to pull but drags this towards square leg to take a run.
Fuller on off, Denly defends it well.
Good length ball on middle, Denly works it towards the leg side.
Good fuller ball on off, Denly walks across a bit to push it off the front foot.
Outside off on a length, Burns pushes this towards the cover fielder.
Length ball on middle and leg, Burns pushes it towards mid on.
Fuller this time outside off, Burns tries to block it out but the ball goes to gully off the outer half of his bat.
Bouncer this one outside off, Burns ducks under it.
On the pads of Burns, he flicks it towards square leg and takes a couple.
Length ball just outside off, Rory pushes it towards mid off. 2 runs off the over.
Good length delivery outside off, Denly lets it be.
Ouch! That must have hurt Denly. The ball shoots up after pitching on middle, Joe tries to block it out but the ball hits his glove and then his stomach. He looks a bit rocked by it.
Outside off, Denly leaves this one alone.
On the pads of Denly, he flicks it towards fine leg and takes a single.
Another one on the pads, this time to Burns. He also flicks it towards fine leg and takes a single.
On the hips, Denly glances this one towards backward square leg and keeps the strike.
Length ball on off pole, Denly defends it.

Woah! What happened on this ball? Did it come off the crack on the surface? It pitched on a length and swung in quickly. The ball hit Denly's inside edge and then onto the box. Awkward scenes out here.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Outside off again, Denly leaves it alone.
Length ball outside off, Denly shoulders arms to it.
Fuller on middle and off, pushed to mid off, maiden by Siddle.
Flat and way outside off, the ball pitches and turns away. Burns plays an awkward cut but straight to the cover fielder.
FOUR! Too short and Burns punishes Lyon as he rocks onto the back foot and cuts this through point for a boundary.
On the pads this time, Burns flicks it towards square leg and rotates the strike.
Full and on the legs, pushed towards mid on.
Again tossed up and on the pads, Lyon pushes this one towards mid-wicket and crosses ends.
Short and outside off, Burns gets an under edge onto it and the ball goes very low near the keeper. It goes behind him and Warner from first slip mops it up.

DROPPED! David Warner, of all the people. Unlucky is now becoming the nickname of Siddle. Super ball in the channel outside off, on a length. Denly has a poke with hard hands and gets an outside edge which flies to David Warner at first slip. He goes to his right slightly slowly as the ball dips but can't hold on that one. A missed opportunity there.
Shortish one this time on middle, Denly works it towards mid on to take a run.
Blocks this outside off ball off his front foot.
On the middle and leg line, Burns works it towards fine leg.
Beaten this time! Good bowling from Siddle as he is consistently bowling in that channel outside off.
Fuller in length outside off, Burns punches it to cover.
Tossed up outside off, Denly takes a stride forward and tries to play it towards the on side. It hits his pads as he misses the flick and the ball goes to Warner at first slip.
Floated on leg, Denly nudges it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
This one short and outside off, Burns goes onto the back foot and guides it towards third man. Cummins there misfields and allows the batters to take two.
FOUR! Shorter than the last one and outside off, this time Burns makes full use of it and cuts it towards covers for a boundary.

Loud appeal by the Aussies for LBW but umpire Aleem Dar turns it down. Lyon bowls this one shorter and on middle and off. It goes in with the angle and hits Burns on the front pad as he misses to defend it. The Aussies appeal in unison but the umpire shakes his head. They think about going for the review but ultimately decide against it. The replays roll in, Hawk Eye comes into play and it shows THREE REDS! This could well prove to be a turning point in this match.
The batsman gives this a full swing of the bat, and connects. They manage to come back for the second.
Good length outside off, Denly leans and blocks it towards point.
Fuller ball on the stumps, Denly looked to flick this hard but is beaten to get hit on the pads. Ooohs and aaahs there but this was going down. Went to fine leg as the batsman change ends.
Shortish one on off, Burns taps this towards the off side.
Beaten but a no ball! Siddle oversteps there. This was in the channel outside off, Burns wanted to smash this but is beaten.
Outside off again on a good length, Burns leaves it alone.
This is slightly fuller, Burns pats it towards point.
A bumper but Siddle has got the direction wrong. Going down leg and too high. Burns ducks under it.
Tossed up just outside off, the ball pitches and moves away from Denly. He misses as he defends inside the line. Even Paine behind the stumps is not able to collect this one.
Tossed up full and on leg, pushed to mid on.
FOUR! Great shot dancing down the track by Denly. Lyon tosses it up on middle and leg, Joe comes down the track and lofts it over mid on for a boundary.

Run out chance! Safe! More luck for England. Denly pushes this full ball towards mid on and sets off for a single. However, Burns is caught ball-watching and does not even take a start. Denly is almost within handshaking distance with his partner but has to stop. He now turns to go back and luckily for him, Usman Khawaja at mid on is slow to throw it to the keeper's end. Denly manages to get back in time. England living dangerously here. Burns should concentrate more on trusting his partner rather than watch the ball.
Short ball and on middle and leg, Denly pulls this towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Slightly shorter around off, Denly taps it towards gully.
Misses his line this time. Pitches this on middle and the ball goes further down towards Paine as Denly misses the flick.
FOUR BYES! Poor stuff this from Siddle. Another one going down the leg side. Denly missed his flick there. Paine dives to his left to stop that but it is too far from him. 50 up for Australia.
Fullish ball on off and middle, Denly looks to drive this but gets an inside edge which hits the pad. There's an appeal but a mild one.
FOUR! Siddle produces an outside edge by pitching this on middle and off on a good length. The ball flies between slip and gully for a boundary. No luck for Siddle as yet.
Outside off, left alone.
Full ball on the pads of Burns, he flicks it towards backward square leg and rotates the strike.
Good length ball just outside off, played towards the cover fielder.
Length ball just outside off, Denly guides it towards the point fielder.
On the pads of Denly, he tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Short and outside off, Denly looks to cut but misses out on it. Could have resulted in some runs here.

Short ball this time by Hazlewood, Denly goes for the risky pull and top edges it. Luckily, the ball falls short of Travis Head at mid-wicket and the batters cross ends. No need for Denly to play such shots.
A short ball wide outside off, left alone.

Full and outside off, Denly looks to drive but the ball scoots off the outside edge past gully towards third man. Three runs taken. 50-RUN STAND IS UP! Consecutive ones for these two. They added 66 in the first innings.
Full ball on middle and off, Rory tucks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
FOUR! Full and on the pads of Denly, he just rotates his wrists and plays a classy flick towards the mid-wicket fence.

OUT! Caught and bowled! Siddle gets Denly and England are three down now. Siddle bowls this one on a good length just outside off, he rolls his finger on it and the ball gets slow off the pitch as a result. Denly is early into his shot and the ball goes uppishly towards Siddle and he makes no mistake in taking the catch with both his hands. England 3 down with just 64 runs on the board (Lead by 72).
Outside off, Stokes lets this one be.
Short to start. Outside off, Burns cuts it through the covers for a single.
Outside off, looks to cut, does Stokes but he gets an under edge which bounces between Tim Paine's legs behind. Two runs taken.

EDGED, FOUR! Late reaction from Warner. Full and around middle, Stokes looks to defend but gets squared up. Warner initially moves to his left at slip, then goes to his right but the extra second costs him. The ball goes past his right hand behind, to the third man fence.
Close! Outside off, Ben looks to cut but almost misses. Gets a bottom edge towards point.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.

EDGED, DROPPED! David Warner again. Full and around off, Stokes looks to defend but the ball spins off the rough, takes the outside edge and flies to Warner at first slip. He has actually moved a step closer to Paine and hence has to dive to his left to take the catch. Had he stayed at his original position, he would have gobbled it. He is furious with himself. What an over from Lyon.
Full on middle and leg, Burns pushes this back to Siddle.

OUT! CAUGHT! Siddle gets another one and in a surprising turn of events, it is Australia who are now on top. Siddle pitches this one on the leg pole on a length. The ball pitches and drifts away from Burns. He tries to defend at it off the front foot but gets a fine outside edge on it and Paine takes an easy catch behind the wickets. Australia jump with joy and England in deep trouble here. England effectively here 79/4.
First ball faced by Buttler, he leaves it alone.
Fuller this time around off, Buttler blocks it out.

This time fuller on the pads of Buttler, he flicks it nonchalantly towards mid-wicket. Head there dives to his right and gets some hand on it, slowing the pace down. He gets up and runs back and the batters take three in the meantime.
Stokes lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Fuller ball outside off, Butter looks to work it around off side but gets an inside edge on the pads.
Slightly fuller again, Buttler blocks it well towards point.

What are you doing, Buttler? Dances down the track to this middle and leg good length ball but misses the flick and is hit on the pad. The ball rolls towards fine leg and the batters cross ends. Lucky there that he got a tickle on the pads or he would've been stumped.
Tossed up outside off, Stokes leaves the ball alone.
Shorter this time and on off, Stokes goes on the back foot and blocks it out.
Full and outside off, Stokes pushes this towards mid off.
Full ball on off, pushed to mid off by Buttler.
Short and outside off, Buttler leaves it alone. The ball swung way too much after the ball went past Buttler and Paine dives to his right to grab it.
Length ball just outside off, it pitches and nips away from him. Buttler is beaten by the away movement on the ball.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.

LEADING EDGE, RUN OUT CHANCE, BOTH SAFE! Ohhh... things are happening. Full and outside off, swinging in, Buttler looks to flick but the ball takes the leading edge and goes over Siddle. Stokes looks for the single but Buttler is busy searching for the ball. Stokes has to turn and meanwhile mid on gets across and has a throw at the bowler's end but it is pretty wide! The big Ben dives in.
Outside off, left alone.
Full on off, Stokes lunges to block it back to the bowler.
That spit off the surface. Pitched on the rough on off and went high in the gloves of Paine.

Good length ball on leg, Stokes looks to punch through mid-wicket but is hit on the pads. That looked going down the leg side but surprisingly Hawk Eye suggests it was hitting the leg pole. No reviews from Australia.
Another one that lands on the rough and goes away from the batsman, Stokes does nothing.
Works this towards fine leg to take a run.
Buttler taps this good length ball on the off side comfortably.
MORE LUCK! A length ball, down the leg side, Stokes looks to flick but gets a leading edge which balloons over square leg! A single taken.
A length ball outside off, watchfully defended.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Full and outside off, driven through the covers for a run.
Outside off, angling away, left alone.
Walks down the track and defends.
Outside off, spinning in, Buttler looks to cut but gets a bottom edge onto his pads.
Full and outside off, Jos drives this through the covers but Travis Head dives to his right and makes an excellent stop.
Tossed up, outside off, driven to the left of Josh Hazlewood at mid off.
Around middle, pushed towards the bowler.
Floated, around middle, solidly blocked towards cover.
Around off, pushed towards point.
On a length around middle and leg, Stokes lets it go on length and it goes over his stumps.
Outside off, left alone.
Walks into the shot and pushes this towards mid on.
A length ball, down the leg side, Ben looks to tuck it to the leg side but misses and is hit on the pads. He is searching for the ball and then gets back in his crease.
Now an inside edge. A length ball, around middle, BS looks to tuck it to the leg side but misses and is hit on the pads off an inside edge.
Outside off, left alone.
Down the leg side, nudged through fine leg. Pat Cummins races all the way from deep backward square leg and dives to his right to stop the ball. Three runs taken.
Outside off, punched back to the bowler.
Full and around middle, blocked watchfully.
Down the leg side, tucked towards fine leg for a single.
Flicks this towards mid-wicket for a run.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Fullish ball on fourth stump line, Buttler blocks it off his front foot.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Buttler pushes it towards mid on.
Beaten! Gets the batsman to play by pitching the ball closer to the off stump, it straightened a bit as it came closer to the bat. Buttler was lucky not to edge that one.
FOUR LEG BYES! Poor one now! Pitches this on middle and leg and seamed further down the leg side. Buttler misses his flick but the ball kisses the pads and go fine for a boundary.
Fullish one on middle and leg, Buttler works this towards mid-wicket and take a couple.
Wide outside off on fifth stump, Buttler left it alone.
Full and around middle, watchfully defended.
How did that miss the off stump? Full and outside off, just missing the rough, Stokes lets it go and the ball goes straight on, just missing the off stick by inches!
This one darts in after pitching on the rough, Ben looks to defend but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Full and down the leg side, flicked through mid-wicket for a run.
Around off, solidly defended.
Shortish one outside off, Stokes looks to power this through cover but mistimes it onto the pitch.
Full on middle this time, Stokes works it nicely towards mid-wicket and run a couple.
Beaten! Swing and miss from Stokes. This is not needed right now with just a few overs left for the day. Wide outside off, Stokes again goes hard at the ball, gets beaten.
Good shot that but finds the fielder in the mid off region.
FOUR! On the pads from Cummins as Stokes works it fine down the leg side to get a four.
Outside off this time from Cummins, Stokes lets it be.
Fullish just outside off pole, Buttler pushes it to the cover fielder.
Outside off, left alone by Buttler.
Again a length ball outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to it.
Fuller this time, the ball pitches and moves away from Jos.
Finally Hazlewood attacks the stumps, it pitches on a good length on off. Jos blocks it out.
Again outside off, Buttler lets it go. Maiden by Josh but the Australians need a wicket here so that they can end the day on a good note.
Length ball outside off, Stokes lets it be. It seems that the English players are trying every way possible to waste some time as we see Ben Stokes tapping the pitch before the start of the over.
Defended off the back foot by Stokes and it looks like the heavens have opened up as well. That's it! STUMPS ON DAY 4!
Play and a miss to begin the day. Cummins steams in and hits the deck hard outside off, Stokes has a slash at it but misses.
Back of a length and outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Bounce and swing on this one. Good length ball outside off, Stokes covers his off stump and leaves it alone. There is late inswing on this one. Paine takes it around his head towards his right.
Length ball outside off, Stokes once again has a slash but misses. One of the biggest overs this as it started on Day 4 and ended on Day 5 after an hour's delay.
First run of the day. Off spinner on off, Buttler turns it behind square on the leg side with the spin and gets a single.
Flighted outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Slightly shorter on off and middle, Stokes defends off the back foot.
Floated outside off, Ben shoulders arms to his one.
Sharp spin on this one. It is pitched on off and spins away, Stokes defends it towards cover with the spin.
Flatter and quicker on middle and leg, Stokes looks to defend but it goes off the inner half of his bat towards square leg for a single. Stokes will keep the strike.
Good length ball on top of middle and off, Stokes gets on his back foot and defends it.

EDGED AND FOUR! Nicely bowled this by Cummins. He bowls a pacy full ball outside off, tempting Stokes to drive. He obliges but gets a thick outside edge. It flies to the right of gully, Khawaja there dives on that side but cannot get his hand to it. The ball races away to the third man fence for a boundary.

FOUR! This is right off the meat. Brutal hitting. Good length ball outside off, Stokes picks the length early and flat-bats it wide of short cover. Wade there does not even move as he had little to no time to react. The ball goes wide and over him to the fence.
Peach of a delivery! Length ball on the fourth stump line, it nips back in a lot after pitching. Stokes though shows his awareness and leaves it alone. The ball just about misses his front pad.
Not much swing on this one, it is outside off and calmly left.
On the fourth stump line, Stokes does not tease that one.
Tossed up on off, Buttler defends it off the front foot.
Flighted on off, Buttler blocks it out.
Slightly short and turning in, Buttler defends it off the back foot towards cover against the spin.
Off spinner pitching on off, Buttler glances it with the spin towards fine leg for a single.
Arm ball outside off, Ben gets on his front foot and leaves it alone.
Shorter on off, Ben calmly defends it to get through the over.
Good length ball around off, Buttler defends it towards point.
On a length very close to the off pole, Buttler keeps his eyes on the ball and defends it.
Fuller on off, Jos Buttler pushes it to cover.
Cummins maintains his off stump line to Buttler. This is served full, Jos defends it to the left of mid off.
Good length ball outside off, Jos has nothing to do with it.
Length ball around off, Buttler defends it towards cover-point to get through the over unscathed. Maiden for Pat.
Shorter on off, Stokes gets on his back foot and defends it onto the ground.
Flatter on off, Stokes defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up on off and middle, Ben strokes it to mid on.

FOUR! Well placed and very well timed. Tossed up on off, Stokes just times it wide of mid on. He does not use power but just pure timing. Hazlewood gives it a chase from mid on and puts in a dive to pull it back but he fails in his attempt to do so.
Follows it up with a calm back foot defense.
Shorter on off, BS keeps it out.
Good length ball outside off, Cummins wants Buttler to go for a drive but Jos says no and leaves it.
Outside off and once again Jos is not interested.

Appeal for LBW but turned down. Full on middle and leg, Buttler looks to flick but misses. The ball hits him flush on the pads. There is an appeal from the Australian players but nothing from the umpire. It looked to be going down the leg and hence no review. Smart bowling this though, outside off, outside off and then one on the stumps.
Fuller on off, Buttler blocks it off the front foot.
Short ball down the leg side, it does not raise as much. Buttler though ducks under it. Paine dives to his left and takes a good carry.
Length ball outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.
Short around off, Stokes hangs back on his back foot and punches it to sweeper cover for one.
Off spinner on off, Buttler glances it to short leg.
Floated on off, Buttler tucks it to short leg.
Flighted outside off, Buttler looks to drive it to the off side but it goes off the inner half of his bat towards mid-wicket.
Floats one on the pads, Buttler glances it to the on side.
Loopy ball on off, JB defends it to get through the over.

NOT OUT! Inside edge detected by the Ultra Edge! Waste of a review by the Australian team. This is a good length ball, seems to be pitching outside leg. The ball hits the inside edge of Stokes' bat and then onto the pads. However, the Australians gambled on this one and thought that the ball hit the pads directly. They think about it and go for the review at the last second. The replays roll in and the Ultra Edge shows that the ball has hit the bat first. Stokes survives. Also, the Hawk Eye comes in later and shows that the ball pitched outside leg. Had it not hit the bat of Stokes, he was still safe. Australia lose one of their reviews.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Beaten! Stokes tries to play at this ball outside off but fails.
Length ball on top of middle, Stokes just helps it towards mid-wicket for a single.
This one keeps low, something similar in the first Test was the undoing for Buttler. This time Jos keeps his eyes on the ball and defends it late.
Good length delivery on off, Buttler defends it off the front foot to get through the over.
Shorter around off, Stokes defends it off the front foot.

EDGED AND FOUR! That was not far away from Warner at first slip. Tossed up outside off, Stokes falls in the honey trap to drive. The ball turns away and finds the thick outside edge of Ben's willow. It flies to the left of Warner at first slip who dives but it goes wide of him and to the third man fence for a boundary.
Shorter on off, Stokes keeps it out.
On the pads, BS flicks it to the on side.
Once again on the pads, Ben tucks it to mid-wicket.
Jaffa to end the over. This is pitched around off and turns in sharply. Stokes looks to defend but misses and the ball goes onto hit the thigh pad of Stokes.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.
Back of a length ball on off, JB defends it off the back foot.
Length ball around off, Buttler stands tall and punches it wide of cover for one.
Nicely bowled. Hazlewood hits the deck hard around off, Stokes looks to defend it inside the line and the away movement sees the ball go to the keeper.
Outside off, Stokes shoulders arms to it.
Fuller on middle, Stokes comes down the track and taps it back to the bowler.
Shorter around off, Buttler nudges it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up around off, Jos gets on his front foot and keeps it out.
Flighted around off, Buttler drives it through point and gets a couple to take the partnership to 49.
Floated on off, Buttler looks to drive but it goes to the on side off the inner half of his blade.
Flighted outside off, Buttler looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto his body.
Tossed up away from the off stump, Buttler leaves it alone.

Short length ball on the leg pole, Stokes pulls it towards square leg for a single. 50-run stand up between Stokes and Buttler. This stand has tilted the match back in the balance. England will be looking to get a move on from here on if they want to stand any chance of winning this match.
Length ball outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.
Full and on the pads of Buttler, he flicks it towards deep mid-wicket and the batters take a couple.
Again outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to it.
Length ball just outside off, Buttler pushes it towards the point fielder.
Bouncer to end the over, Buttler ducks under it and the ball goes to Tim Paine behind the stumps.
Good length ball on middle and off, Stokes pushes it with soft hands towards covers and takes a single.
FOUR! Full and tossed up outside off, Buttler leans into the drive and caresses the ball through the cover region for a boundary.
Full and tossed up on middle and leg, pushed back to Lyon.
Flat on off and middle, goes towards the off side off the outside half of the bat.
Full and floated, Buttler pushes it back to the bowler.
Length ball just outside off, pushed to point off the back foot.

FOUR! MAJESTIC! All of a sudden, England are playing with renewed vigour. Full and around middle, Stokes drives this straight back. Hazlewood tries stopping it with his right hand, putting half a bend, but the ball whizzes past. The lead is 140 now.
Length ball just outside off, pushed back towards the bowler. Hazlewood bends and tries to get a hand to it but fails to do so as the ball goes towards mid on.
Length ball just outside off, Stokes pulls it towards mid-wicket and gets a single.

EDGED AND FOUR! Buttler gets lucky on this one. Pitched full and on off, Buttler goes for a cover drive but gets a thick outside edge as the ball goes between gully and the slip cordon to the third man fence.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Length ball on the off pole, Buttler defends it off the back foot.
Floated on middle, Stokes looks to defend but he does so off the inner half of his bat.
Flighted on the stumps, Stokes gets forward and defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Ben keeps it out.
Short around off, Stokes gets on his back foot and punches it to cover for one.
Shorter on the stumps, Stokes gets on his back foot and keeps it out.

Excellent running. These two know each other well and that was visible here. Floated delivery on the pads, Stokes glances it towards fine leg. The fielder from square leg gives it a chase and pulls it back before the ropes. Stokes and Buttler are both quick between the wickets, they look for the third and get it with ease.
Wide and full outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
This time a touch short, Stokes pushes it towards mid off.
Beaten! Good length ball just outside off, Stokes looks to push at it but does so inside the line and misses.
Well outside off, Stokes lets it be.

Very well left from Stokes. Siddle comes steaming in and delivers a length ball around off, Stokes comes down the track and then shoulders arms to it. You seldom see that and this shows the confidence this man is carrying.
Fuller on middle and leg, defended towards the leg side by Stokes. Good start by Siddle.
Flat and on the pads of Buttler, he blocks it out.
Full and tossed up outside off, Buttler blocks it out.

This is pitched on the leg pole, it turns in and hits the pads of Buttler. It loops towards short leg and he dives to catch it but isn't able to do so. Leg bye taken as the ball rolls towards fine leg.
The ball pitches just outside the off pole and spins away, Stokes is beaten by the turn as he looks to defend.
That ball has taken the inside edge of the batsman and thudded into his pads.
On the pads of Stokes, he flicks it towards mid on and keeps the strike. The lead is now 150.
Good length ball on off, Stokes defends it towards cover.
Length ball on middle and off pole, Stokes comes down the track and tries to hit the ball towards mid on. It takes the leading edge of his bat and the ball goes to point and the batters take two.
On the pads of Stokes, he flicks it down the leg side.
Length ball on middle and off, Stokes plays it back towards the bowler.
Comes down the track this time and Siddle pulls his length short. Stokes adjusts at the last moment and defends it out.
Length ball outside off, Stokes looks to push it towards covers. It takes the leading edge of his blade and the ball goes towards third man as the batters take one.
Shorter on off, Stokes continues to defend Lyon of his back foot.

FIFTY FOR BEN STOKES! His 19th in Test cricket. He has continued his good form and once again when England were in trouble, Stokes raises his hands up and delivers. Short around off, Stokes cuts it to point and gets to his milestone. He raises his bat and soaks in all the applause.
FOUR! Creamed away! Floated on off, Buttler gets on his front foot and drives it beautifully through covers for a boundary.
Floated on off, Buttler follows the boundary with a single towards cover.
Tossed up outside off, Stokes lets it go.
Flights one on off, Stokes defends it off the front foot.
Length ball just outside off, Buttler walks a bit down the track and the ball hits the inside edge of his bat and onto the pads.
Outside off, left alone by Buttler.
Good length ball this time, Buttler pushes it nicely towards the cover fielder.
Wide outside off stump, the batsman leaves it alone.
Outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.

FOUR LEG BYES! Length ball just outside the leg pole, Buttler looks to flick but misses. The ball hits his pads and goes towards the fine leg fence. Umpire Gaffaney waits for the Australian team to finish their decision on taking the LBW review and then signals leg byes.

WOW! That one has kept low and somehow managed to miss the stumps too. It is pitched on the rough outside off, Stokes looks to defend but the ball keeps very low and goes under Stokes' defensive bat on to the keeper.
Floated on middle, Stokes defends it off the front foot.
Floated outside off, Stokes looks to defend with soft hands. The ball takes the outside edge and goes wide of a diving first slip for a single.
Floated around off, Buttler looks to defend but misses.

In the air and just wide. Tossed up on middle, Buttler drives it uppishly as the ball sticks onto the surface. Luckily he pushes it way wide, to the right of the bowler. Lyon dives but cannot get close. The batsmen take a single as the  fielder from long on gathers it.
Flighted on off, Ben keeps it out to get to Lunch without any casualties.
Starts the new session with an unwelcoming bouncer. It is around middle and leg, Buttler sits under it.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler continues his cautious approach and leaves it alone.
Fuller on the fifth stump line, Buttler leaves it alone.
Second bouncer of the over and it is also closer to the body. Buttler picks it early and ducks under it.
On the fourth stump line and fuller in length. Jos offers no stroke.
Gets bat on ball for the first time in this session. Back of a length ball on off, Buttler gets on his toes and keeps it down.
Floated on off, Stokes keeps it out.

That has spun leaps and bounds. It is pitched on the rough and spins away. Stokes looks to drive but misses. Paine too cannot gather it as the ball deflects off his gloves towards the third man region for one. They steal a bye.
Excellent shot but straight to the man at cover. Flighted on off, Buttler drives it hard but cannot get it past the fielder at short cover.
Floated on the stumps, Buttler gets behind it and blocks it.
On the pads, Buttler glances it to mid-wicket with the spin.
Shorter on top of off, Jos defends it to get through the over.
Back of a length ball outside off, Stokes lets it carry to the keeper.

Excellent running, Good length ball on middle, Stokes tucks it with soft hands towards mid-wicket and immediately calls for two. The ball is to the left of the fielder and the duo of Buttler and Stokes is quick so they manage to get the second with ease.
Short ball which rises just over the belly. It is down the leg side, Stokes goes for the pull but misses.
Length delivery on off, Ben strokes it to point and gets to the other end.
On a length around off, Buttler nudges it to point.

OUT! Caught! Buttler's patient innings comes to end. The short ball does the trick here and Cummins has ended this building stand. Cummins bangs it in short around the body. Buttler goes for the pull but gets a top edge on it. It goes high and straight to deep backward square leg. Hazlewood there hardly moves an inch and takes a simple catch. Soft dismissal for Buttler, he would be gutted to get out in such a fashion especially after taking his time out in the middle.
On the pads, Stokes glances it to the on side for a single.
Play and miss! Floated outside off, Bairstow looks to drive but misses. Not an ideal start to the innings for Jonny.

Bairstow is off the mark with some help by the misfield. Tossed up on off, Bairstow strokes it to the right of mid off. Head there moves and dives to his right but fails to gather the ball. It deflects towards mid on and they take a single.
